<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17700] CoreContainer does not obtain a lock when unloading cores</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17700</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CoreContainer uses &lt;tt&gt;solrCores.waitAddPendingCoreOps(name)&lt;/tt&gt; when doing an operation on a core. And the documentation for &lt;tt&gt;SolrCores.waitAddPendingCoreOps(name)&lt;/tt&gt; mentions that:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;// Wait here until any pending operations (load, unload or reload) are completed on this core.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, CoreContainer does not use this locking when unloading a core. This is the reason why we are seeing race condition issues when deleting and reloading a collection at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Loading a core can possibly require unloading said core, when &quot;deleteUnknownCoresOnStartup&quot; is used, thus we need a way of unloading without a lock. But other than this edge case, locking the unload operation should only improve stability in Solr.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
